TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));


Find a formula for \( f^{-1}(x) \)  if : 
$BR
\( f(x) = - \sqrt{1 - x} \) $BR

\( f^{-1}(x) \) =  \{ ans_rule(40) \}.
$BR

$BR
\( \left(f^{-1}\right)'(x) = \) \{ ans_rule(40) \}.


EOT

ANS(fun_cmp("1 - x^2", [2,3], vars=>["x"]));
ANS(fun_cmp("-2x", [2,3], vars=>["x"]));

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT')); 

$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD Set \( y = - \sqrt{1
- x} \), solve for x to see \( x = 1 - y^2 \), and set \( f^{-1}(y) =
1 - y^2 \), then \( f^{-1}(x) = 1 - x^2 \) .

EOT



